{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a7b27875-4e55-4a39-8b11-8c00d2fd775a","content":"The directory appears empty, so I'll answer from knowledge:\n\nTo switch from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform with MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0, you just need to **remove** (or set to `false`) the `UseVSTest` property:\n\n```xml\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <TargetFramework>net8.0</TargetFramework>\n    <!-- Remove or set to false: -->\n    <!-- <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest> -->\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n1. **MSTest.Sdk 3.4+** uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform **by default** — `UseVSTest` was opting you back into the legacy runner.\n2. Simply deleting `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` enables the new platform.\n3. Run tests with `dotnet test` as before (the SDK wires up the new runner automatically).\n4. If you use `dotnet test` with solution filters or need VS Test Explorer integration, add:\n   ```xml\n   <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n   ```\n   (already implied by the SDK, but explicit if needed).\n\n5. **Breaking changes to watch for:**\n   - `.runsettings` files still work but some legacy adapter settings may be ignored.\n   - Custom test adapters targeting VSTest won't load; look for Microsoft.Testing.Platform equivalents.\n   - CLI output format changes slightly (use `--report-trx` for TRX output).","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e176165a-0741-4209-9936-a8e7910086a7","outputTokens":382,"requestId":"BC2E:5FB6B:1C27DAF:1F3BA81:69FA9098"},"id":"e4f059f4-7bd0-4a71-9e1f-46fb455c8a73","timestamp":"2026-05-06T00:51:46.696Z","parentId":"bc8fbabd-4ead-43b3-bd5b-7f9541d4832e"}
